### âš™ï¸ Request Flow
1. Request Validation: Checks if request is valid (URL, headers, payload).
2. Middleware:
   - Auth (JWT, API keys)
   - Rate limiting & throttling
   - SSL termination
   - Logging & monitoring
   - CORS, IP whitelisting/blacklisting
3. Routing: Maps paths to services (e.g. `/users/- â†’ user-service`).
4. Backend Communication: Routes request (HTTP/gRPC, etc.) to the right service.
5. Response Transformation: Converts backend responses into client-friendly formats (e.g. gRPC â†’ JSON).
6. Caching: Optional â€” speeds up repeated non-user-specific requests using TTL or Redis.
